explanation: The solution utilizes a HashSet to efficiently track unique integers covered by the intervals. It iterates through each interval and adds all integers within its range to the HashSet. The size of the HashSet represents the count of unique integers present in at least one interval. The time complexity is determined by the nested loops iterating through intervals and their respective ranges. The space complexity is also dominated by the HashSet storing unique integers.

